reviewText: Love the look of the movie, great action.

Until it decided to not work about an hour into the movie. I've tried several times to get it to get past that point to no avail. Should've watched it sooner so that I could have returned it. Now I'm stuck with a movie that won't finish. What a waste of time and especially money.
Just as good as the first Sin City... I love a movie with a good story and unusual presentation... I call it one of my "artsy-fartsy" movies... I watch every now and then along with the 1st one...
Great experience! Received quickly and without damage
Great follow up to the original  5 stars
If you're a Sin City fan, the sequel finishes the storyline.  The cinematography is just as good as the original.
Not the the original Sin City, but still a decent sequel.
love sin city on big screen
Not as good as the first one, but entertaining.
A bit on the crazy side.  Didn't expect it to have so much in black and white.  Really is an off-the-wall movie and does take a bit of watching to get the gist of the story.
How can you NOT love Eva Green in this!

Everything about this movie met my expectations. I own the 1st Sin City and this prequel is absolutely amazing. I don't have the time to express my love for this picture. The best way to say is: Frank Miller's fans: buy both movies - they are so worthy!
